<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-065-810  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 065 810.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC World  March 1989 v7 n3 p156(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Prodigy. (Software Review) (News and electronic mail service)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Getts, Judy.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Prodigy is an on-line information retrieval system marketed bySears Roebuck and IBM.andP;  It differs from other on-line service inits low monthly flat access charge of $9.95.andP;  It offers news andstock information in a graphic format similar to videotext.andP;  Itdisplays color only with an Enhanced Graphics Adapter card, anddoes not yet support IBM's video graphics array.andP;  Access toProdigy requires 512-kbytes of RAM, without the presence of othermemory resident programs.andP;  The news service is limited inusefulness and the service's electronic mail system is limited tomessages of 250 words or less.andP;  Prodigy subscribers need a startupkit that sells for $49.95 and is available only in limited areas.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (services)Sears, Roebuck and Co. (services).andO;Ticker:    S; IBM.andO;Topic:     Information Storage and RetrievalOn-LineData BasesTelephone Banking.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>